    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute><dateline>April 7. - 91:</dateline></opener>
                <p>I will feed &amp; feed you during our existence with the overflowings of my brains: as for example with what attends this.<note type="editorial">The enclosure suggested here has not survived with the manuscript letter.</note>
                    As to <rs type="art" ref="ar0240">Lady Salisbury</rs> I thank you for the Princely gift: but return her Ladyship as of no use. a Dowager 
                    <rs type="art" ref="ar0240">Lady S.</rs> I have bought (in her weeds) <del><gap unit="letters" quantity="1" reason="illegible"/></del> will suit my 
                    <hi rend="underline"><bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0032">journey to London</title></bibl></hi>. So get <del><gap unit="letters" quantity="2" reason="illegible"/></del>one
                    from <persName ref="pe0423">Richardson</persName>. I am above selling my books to any but Booksellers. If you wish to pay me, try to get me 
                    <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0118">a Hague edition of Monfau<del><gap unit="letters" quantity="3" reason="illegible"/></del>con's mon. Fr.</title></bibl> but Pray leave off that
                    Princely usage of an order for the Day That <persName ref="pe0232">Pennant</persName> <hi rend="underline">be</hi>, or <hi rend="underline">be not let in</hi>.<note type="editorial">Pennant's play on word revolves around the meaning of the term 'letting in' in the context of extra-illustration – i.e. to insert material onto pages – and in reference, possibly, to a copy of a <rs type="art" ref="ar0235">portrait of himself</rs>.</note></p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Adieu
                    <lb/>Y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> truely</salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">T Pennant</persName></signed>
                    <dateline><hi rend="underline">April 7<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.</hi></dateline>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>My <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0266">2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> vol. of France</title></bibl>
                    shall be y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> next repast.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><address>
                    <addrLine><persName ref="pe0313">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Bull</persName>, <placeName ref="pl0759">stratton | <hi rend="underline">street</hi></placeName></addrLine>
                    </address></p>
            </div>
